HEADWORD: Selenography
<hw>Sel`e*nog"ra*phy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>selh`nh</grk> the moon + <ets>-graphy</ets>.]</ety> <def>The
science that treats of the physical features of the moon; --
corresponding to <xex>physical geography</xex> in respect to the
earth.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Accurate <xex>selenography</xex>, or description of
the moon.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Sir T. Browne. </au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

